# SPA fallback for client-side routing is handled by Cloudflare Pages' native
# 200.html mechanism (generated in the build output by scripts/prerender.js),
# NOT by a wildcard rewrite. The old `/*  /index.html  200` rule was rejected by
# Pages with "Infinite loop detected" (since /index.html itself matches /*), so it
# never took effect. Prerendered routes (react-snap) ship their own
# /<route>/index.html static files, and any unmatched path falls back to 200.html.
#
# API requests are routed to Pages Functions via public/_routes.json
# ("include": ["/api/*"]) and are never served the SPA shell.
